22/08/2003
MODRICA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The armies of BIH's two entities agreed on a plan Thursday (21 August) for downsizing the number of professional staff.
In the end, there will be 8,000 professional soldiers and commanders in the BiH Federation and 4,000 in Republika Srpska.
The entities also plan to cut the length of military service for conscripts from six months to four.
Outdated weapons will be sold and some military units and warehouses closed.
(SRNA, Onasa, Dnevni Avaz - 21/08/03)
